    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><div n="1" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Iulia Archidia Iuliana ux<supplied reason="lost">or Ulpi Valeriani vixit</supplied> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>n<am>n</am></abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> XXX&amp;lt;V&amp;gt; <expan><abbr>Ulpi</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan> Valerianus <expan><abbr>eq</abbr><ex>ues</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>R</abbr><ex>omanus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ecit</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/>si quis hunc sarcofagum aperuerit, poen<supplied reason="lost">ae nomine dabit <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></supplied> </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> Ἰουλία Ἀρχιδία Ἰουλιανή γυνὴ Οὐλ<supplied reason="lost">πίου Οὐαλεριανοῦ</supplied> &amp;lt;ζ=Σ&amp;gt;ήσ(ασα) ἔτεσι λε Οὔλπ<supplied reason="lost">ιος Οὐαλεριανὸς <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></supplied> <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> 
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>(B): Am Anfang der Z. 5 stehen, wie von G. Seure gesehen, die Buchstaben ΣΗΣ. Seine Interpetation als [ζήσα]/σης (sic) ist vielleicht weniger überzeugend.</p>
            </div>
